To align a row of divs to the right using Flexbox in CSS, you can use the `justify-content` property with the value `flex-end`. Here's an example:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <style>
    .container {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: flex-end;
    }

    div {
      background-color: lightblue;
      width: 50px;
      height: 50px;
      margin: 10px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <div></div>
    <div></div>
    <div></div>
    <div></div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
```
In this example, the `.container` is a flex container that holds three divs with a blue background color and equal width and height. The `justify-content: flex-end;` property aligns its child divs to the right side of the container. You can add more divs as needed.
